ACT:
 Sugar Cane (Control) Order, 1955---Central Government's power under cl. 6 of Order to regulate supply of sugarcane to factories--Power under cl. 6 delegated under cl. 11 to State Governments and Cane Commissioners-Cane Commissioner passing Order under cl. 6(1) on direction given by Chief Minister such order is invalid--An order under s. 6(1) modifying a reservation in favour of a factory is quasi judicial--Requirement of natural justice must be satisfied.
 
